<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>In This Pile</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/index.css" />
    <script type="module" src="/index.js"></script>
  </head>
  <body>
    <main>
      <p id="date"><%= it.hours %>:<%= it.minutes %>:<%= it.seconds %></p>
      <div id="clock">
        <p>Tell us about the passing of time,</p>
        <p>in this room:</p>
        <p>our fruiting body</p>
        <p>bursts forth,</p>
        <p>life stands in place, covered,</p>
        <p>like a mouse</p>
        <p>or a mushroom</p>
      </div>
      <div id="graph">
        <canvas><%= it.scroll %></canvas>
        <div><%= it.clicks %></div>
      </div>
      <div id="posts">
        <div>
          <p>
            In This Pile is a response to our accelerationist behavior, a space
            to question how we spend time with other forms of life and
            eachother. It is a compost pile in a small room. It’s mycelium,
            metal and plastic. Spores and projected pixels. It’s a body and
            mind. It’s growth and decay. Lines entwined. It’s space to care. A
            room to pause (time) in. It’s now but it’s not.
          </p>
        </div>
        <% it.posts.reverse().forEach((post) => { %>
        <div>
          <h2><%= post.title %></h2>
          <p><%= post.body %></p>
        </div>
        <% }) %>
      </div>
    </main>
    <iframe
      class="livestream"
      src="https://youtube.com/embed/T1LMtq4x7a0?autoplay=1&mute=1&controls=0&iv_load_policy=3&rel=0&showinfo=0&showsearch=0"
      allowfullscreen=""
      width="560"
      height="315"
      frameborder="0"
      style="width: 100%; height: 100vh; position: relative"
    ></iframe>
  </body>
</html>
